radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated hyperemic appendix with surrounding fat stranding and an appendicolith at the base. No fluid collection or free air. The lung bases are clear. No significant abnormalities found in the liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small bowel, colon, intra-abdominal vasculature, bladder, and reproductive organs. A small amount of nonspecific pelvic free fluid.
